.about__wrapper
    .columns.is-centered.is-vcentered.is-is-variable
        .column.is-5-widescreen.is-6-tablet
            .about__img-container
                = image_tag 'https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/nicole-salazar.webp', width: 1080, height: 1350, alt: 'Picture of Nicole Salazar', class: 'about__img'
        .column.is-5-widescreen.is-6-tablet
            .about__text-wrapper
                %h1 Nice to meet you,
                %p
                    I'm Nicole. A designer and front end developer from Dominican Republic, currently based in New York. I'm a life-long artist and lover of experimentation, from contributing work to international projects like
                    %span
                        = link_to "The Phaistos Project", "http://www.45symbols.com/symbols/portfolio/beginners-mind-nicole-salazar/"
                    to 
                    %span
                        = link_to "constructing typography from unconventional materials", "/graphic-design/intimates"
                    I'm drawn to impactful work that pushes past the obvious.
                %p
                    With 7 years of experience, I have worked with a range of clients, budgets, and goals across branding, web, and product design. My work ranges from startups like
                    %span
                        = link_to "Sharelov,","/graphic-design/social-media"
                    a social media marketing platform, to established brands like
                    %span
                        = link_to "Dr. Harvey's,", "/ux-ui/dr-harveys"
                    a holistic pet food company. Across both, the work has covered everything from website redesigns and social media design to expanding and evolving existing web presences.
                %p
                    My approach to design is fun, curious and meticulous. I aim to create useful, engaging and moving design that causes a lasting impression. Some recent work I'm proud of includes the Puerto Rico Open, where I had to learn a new industry from scratch, work within an existing design system and push it somewhere fresher and more modern, all within a tight budget. Another favorite was
                    %span 
                        = link_to "Island Finance,", "/ux-ui/island-finance-web"
                    where the challenge was figuring out how to make something as intimidating as personal finance feel warm, clear, and human.
                %p 
                    I love working closely with brands to understand their vision, values and goals in order to deliver outstanding results. When I'm not designing, I might be dancing salsa, coloring, cooking or reading a book.